Years covered: 2016–2026. Approximately 153 posts.
Major themes identified:
1. Oberon Language & Systems (largest theme, 2019–2022) — "Mostly Oberon"
multi-part series, VirtualBox/QEMU emulation, combining Oberon-07 with C.
2. Go Programming Language (2016–2024) — tooling, ARM cross-compilation,
library-oriented software design.
3. Markdown, Static Site Generation & Web Tooling (all years) — mkpage,
Pandoc, Pagefind, frontmatter, plain-text publishing pipelines.
4. Database & SQL Technologies (2021–present) — SQLite3, PostgreSQL,
PL/pgSQL, rethinking REST APIs.
5. Raspberry Pi & Single-Board Computers (2016–2025) — hardware setup,
OS options, Go and Oberon on Pi hardware.
6. Deno & TypeScript (2024–2025) — Deno 2, transpiling, structured data,
"When Deno, When Go?".
7. Alternative & Retro Operating Systems (2019–2024) — FreeDOS, RISC OS,
NativeOberon, Oberon System 3 via QEMU.
8. Personal Search & Information Management (2022–2025) — personal search
engines, RSS, indexing, knowledge organization.
9. Web Architecture & Philosophy (2024–2026) — simplifying the web,
text-oriented design, RSS, owning infrastructure.
10. LLM / AI Tools (2025–2026) — AI assistant first impressions, building
web components with LLMs, AI at the edge.
Blog arc: Go tooling & Markdown (2016–2018) → deep Oberon (2019–2021) →
databases & info architecture (2021–2023) → web philosophy & AI (2024–2026).


